1.title: Wunsche Cemetery, Texas
1.plot: The first episode of Two Paranormal Guys is here. Join hosts Benny Muniz and Connor Smith as they go on a mission to prove (or disprove) the existence of spirits and the afterlife. They travel to a small family cemetery along Interstate 45 in Spring, Texas, known as the Wunsche Family Cemetery. Their primary target is Olena Wunsche, a woman who was shot in the back and murdered in 1929. Could she be the explanation behind the evidence captured?

2.title: Wunsche Cemetery, Texas Beyond the Grave
2.plot: Join Benny and Connor as they do a post-mortem on the Wunsche Family Cemetery investigation. Witness them argue evidence, explain equipment, or show any behind the scenes content from the show.

3.title: Urban Legends, Texas
3.plot: Benny and Connor do some detective work to find the truth behind some urban legends in the Houston area: the Patterson Street shadows, and the lady of Old Greenhouse Road. Join them as they look to see whether or not these stories have any evidence behind them.

4.title: Urban Legends, Texas Beyond the Grave
4.plot: Benny and Connor discuss the happenings at the investigations of Patterson Street and Old Greenhouse Road. Tune in to see arguments over evidence, explanations of equipment, and behind the scenes clips from Two Paranormal Guys.

5.title: Magnolia Cemetery, Texas
5.plot: Benny and Connor investigate the Witch's Grave at Magnolia Cemetery in Katy, TX. They investigate tales of hexes, shadows, and plenty of other paranormal happenings. Tag along as they see if these tales have any amount of truth to them.

6.title: Magnolia Cemetery, Texas Beyond the Grave
6.plot: Benny and Connor get into further arguments about what actually happened at Magnolia Cemetery in Katy, Texas. Check out some funny behind the scenes clips and some other discussions about the investigation.

7.title: Powder Mill, Texas
7.plot: Benny and Connor enter the site of a former Civil War Powder Mill in Tomball, Texas and witness more than just the supernatural. Join Benny in this very real horror movie, and decide for yourself if somebody is really out there, and who they might be.

8.title: Powder Mill, Texas Beyond the Grave
8.plot: In this journey beyond the grave, Connor and Benny talk about their investigation of Powder Mill Pond in Tomball, Texas. Learn a little more about what exactly happened to Benny during his investigation.

9.title: Old Town Spring, Texas
9.plot: Benny and Connor have a special guest this week...but not the paranormal kind. Caterella joins the TPG Crew as they investigate the Wunsche Bros. Cafe and Saloon as well as claims of a railroad worker haunting the tracks of Old Town Spring just outside of Houston, TX.

10.title: Old Town Spring, Texas Beyond the Grave
10.plot: Caterella joins Benny and Connor on Beyond the Grave. The three will discuss the happenings in Old Town Spring, and in the process argue a bit about what exactly happened that night and the existence of the paranormal as a whole.

11.title: The Social Knitwork, Texas Part 1
11.plot: In two historic firsts for the TPG Crew, we have a two-part episode AND Benny and Connor are actually allowed inside a business. The Social Knitwork in Old Town Spring, Texas, allows them into their shop for an investigation that yields voices, orbs galore, and even Mr. Krabs.

12.title: The Social Knitwork, Texas Part 1 Beyond the Grave
12.plot: Adam Rogers joins Benny and Connor on this Beyond the Grave as they discuss the events that took place in the Social Knitwork during part one of the investigation, and delve a bit further into the possibility of such strong evidence during their first lockdown.

13.title: Social Knitwork, Texas Part 2
13.plot: Benny and Connor are back in part two of the Social Knitwork investigation. Check out what happens when they enter the business alone to face Julius and what happens when they say goodbye to him.

14.title: The Social Knitwork, Texas Part 2 Beyond the Grave
14.plot:

15.title: Huntsville, Texas
15.plot: The final investigation of season one is unfortunately upon us. Benny, Connor, and Enrique make a small drive up north (not east) to Huntsville. Texas. Huntsville, Texas. Gotta reiterate that it's Texas. Not Alabama. Benny drags the group to the statue of Sam Houston and actually ends up making a good call, a Native American chief makes his presence known in a prison cemetery, and the group has another issue with the living making their presence known as well.

16.title: Huntsville, Texas Beyond the Grave
16.plot: The final Beyond the Grave is here - Huntsville. Witness why our investigation was cut short and why Benny may or may not return for season two.
